e of the founder of the only native British religious order (abolished at the Dissolution of the Monasteries),  St Gilbert  of Sempringham (  ?1083–1189 ), in whose honour it is still sometimes bestowed, especially among Roman Catholics. It gained a wider currency in the 19th century."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Gilbert Delaval was born in 1169, in Worcester, Worcestershire, England, his father, Henry Delaval, was 22 and his mother, Mrs. Delaval, was 20. He married Mrs. Gilbert DeLaval about 1193, in Chaddesley Corbett, Worcestershire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 6 sons and 1 daughter. He died in 1194, at the age of 25."},"et":{"1169–1194":"1169–1194","1173–Female":"1173–Surnud","1196–1270":"1196–1270","1198–1270":"1198–1270","1200–Male":"1200–Surnud","1202–1236":"1202–1236","1204–Female":"1204–Surnud","1206–Male":"1206–Surnud","1220–Male":"1220–Surnud","1148–1226":"1148–1226","1150–Female":"1150–Surnud","before 1169":"enne 1169","1220":"1220","1198":"1198","1196":"1196","1173":"1173","1194":"1194","1150":"1150","1270":"1270","1206":"1206","1226":"1226","1204":"1204","1148":"1148","1236":"1236","1169":"1169","1202":"1202","1200":"1200","Abt 1193":"umbes 1193","Worcester, Worcestershire, England":"Worcester, Worcestershire, England","Chaddesley Corbett, Worcester, England":"Chaddesley Corbett, Worcestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Northumberland, England, United Kingdom":"Northumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1169–1194":"1169–1194","1173–Female":"1173–Kuollut","1196–1270":"1196–1270","1198–1270":"1198–1270","1200–Male":"1200–Kuollut","1202–1236":"1202–1236","1204–Female":"1204–Kuollut","1206–Male":"1206–Kuollut","1220–Male":"1220–Kuollut","1148–1226":"1148–1226","1150–Female":"1150–Kuollut","before 1169":"ennen vuotta 1169","1220":"1220","1198":"1198","1196":"1196","1173":"1173","1194":"1194","1150":"1150","1270":"1270","1206":"1206","1226":"1226","1204":"1204","1148":"1148","1236":"1236","1169":"1169","1202